      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The following structure represents a tetrahedral alkoxide ion intermediate formed by addition of a nucleophile to a carboxylic acid derivative. Identify the nucleophile, the leaving group, the starting acid derivative, and the ultimate product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdjhXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3cfe473e4441e19841a0cc89d25648ab1fda793d/OChem_21_02_012.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model of tetrahedral-alkoxide shows cyclopentane connected to methylene, connected to carbon single-bonded to hydroxyl, methoxide, and oxygen atoms. Black, gray, and red spheres denote carbon, hydrogen, and oxygen.\">",
